  { question: 'How should beauty brands prioritize email marketing apps?', answer: 'Follow Replenishment by product usage and Routine education sequences before adding new channels. Buying cycle: 30–90 day replenishment windows; strong subscription potential; shade/variant complexity' },
  { question: 'What metrics matter for beauty brands?', answer: 'Replenishment conversion rate, Subscription retention at 90 days, Bundle attach rate from email, Unsubscribe rate on education vs promo' },
  { question: 'When is tool sprawl risky for beauty brands?', answer: 'When popup, email, SMS, reviews, and loyalty each send conflicting offers without shared suppressions — common when segments overlap.' },
  { question: 'Does Sequenzy replace the whole stack for beauty brands?', answer: 'No — Sequenzy is the lifecycle and automation layer. Capture, SMS, reviews, and loyalty specialists still earn separate slots when those jobs are revenue-critical.' },
