  { question: 'How should beauty brands handle shade matching in email?', answer: 'Post-purchase shade follow-up at day 3–5, not day 1 review asks. Branch on variant purchased — warm undertone buyers get different education than cool. Sequenzy and Klaviyo both support variant-triggered flows when Shopify syncs shade SKUs cleanly.' },
  { question: 'Do beauty subscriptions need different Shopify email marketing apps?', answer: 'The lifecycle layer stays Sequenzy or Klaviyo — subscription management is flow logic, not a separate ESP. Skip/churn prevention emails must suppress when Recharge or Skio already sent portal notifications the same day.' },
  { question: 'What content ratio works for haircare and fragrance brands?', answer: 'Lead with routine education and usage timing, not promo. Track unsubscribe rate on education vs promo sends — if promos spike exits, your replenishment timing is off or colliding with subscription billing emails.' },
  { question: 'Should beauty brands use Yotpo with Sequenzy?', answer: 'Yes when reviews and loyalty drive repeat purchase. Yotpo handles proof collection; Sequenzy owns welcome, replenishment by product usage, and winback. Shared suppressions prevent review requests and replenishment nudges on the same morning.' },
