      <h2>Flow collision notes for beauty teams</h2>
      <p>Beauty stacks often run Sequenzy lifecycle, Yotpo reviews, Recharge subscription emails, and SMS promos simultaneously. Without gates, subscribers get review asks, replenishment nudges, and 20%-off texts the same morning.</p>
      <p><strong>Replenishment vs promo:</strong> Never send discount blasts to subscribers in active replenishment window — you train them to wait for codes. VIP loyalty points emails should suppress during new launch hype weeks.</p>
      <p><strong>Subscription billing day:</strong> Pause marketing sends 24 hours around rebill — collision with failed payment recovery from subscription app creates complaint spikes.</p>
      <p><strong>Shade launch week:</strong> Post-purchase education for recent buyers must exclude new shade promo language — "your order matters" plus "everything new" feels incoherent.</p>
      <p><strong>Salon wholesale accounts:</strong> Suppress all DTC promo flows. B2B pricing and consumer coupons in the same inbox destroy channel trust.</p>
      <p>One retention owner should maintain the collision calendar across Shopify email marketing apps — not three agencies touching separate tools.</p>
